{"word":"κυδρός","slug":"κυδρός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κυδρός</b></el> <el>(κῡδρός, ή, όν) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:κῦδος'><el>κῦδος</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>= <a href='S:κυδάλιμος'><el>κυδάλιμος</el></a>,\n<p/><i>glorious, illustrious, noble</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>; of a horse, <i>proud, stately</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b> (For the <a href='S:irregular'>irreg.</a> <a href='S:Comparative'>comp.</a> and <a href='S:Superlative'>Sup.</a>, <a href='S:vide'>v.</a> <el>κύδιστος.</el>)<p/>"}]}